        <h3 style="margin-top: 25px;" id="demographics">
            Hopkinsville Demographics
        </h3>
    


            
                

                
                <h4>What is the voting age population of Hopkinsville, Kentucky?</h4>
                <p>
                    The total voting age population of Hopkinsville, Kentucky, meaning US citizens 18 or older, is 22,743.  The voting age population is 47.3% male and 52.7% female.
                </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Hopkinsville, Kentucky residents are senior citizens?</h4>
                    <p>
                        According to the latest census statistics, 16.4% of
                        the residents of Hopkinsville are 65 or older.
                    </p>
                

                
                    

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    
                    
                    <h4>What are the racial demographics of Hopkinsville, Kentucky?</h4>
                    <p>The racial demographics of Hopkinsville are 63.4% White, 31.2% Black, 2.3% Two or more races, 1.5% Asian, 0.8% Other, 0.5% American Indian and 0.4% Native Hawaiian or Other Pacific Islander. Additionally, 3.6% of the population identifies as Hispanic.</p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Hopkinsville, Kentucky residents are below the poverty line?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Hopkinsville, 22.4% of
                    residents have an income below the poverty line, and the child poverty rate
                    is 29.7%.
                    On a per-household basis,
                    19.2% of families are below
                    the poverty line in Hopkinsville.
                    </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Hopkinsville, Kentucky residents are in the labor force?</h4>
                    <p>
                    Among those aged 16 and older, 54.9% of
                    Hopkinsville residents are in the labor force.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    

                
                
                <h4>What are the education levels among Hopkinsville, Kentucky residents?</h4>
                <p>Among the adult population 25 years old and over,
                    84.5% of
                    Hopkinsville residents have at least a high school degree or
                    equivalent, 19.6%
                    have a bachelor's degree and 9.0%
                    have a graduate or professional degree.
                

                
                
                <h4>What percentage of Hopkinsville, Kentucky residents speak a non-English language at home?</h4>
                <p>
                Among Hopkinsville residents aged 5 and older, 4.2% of them speak a non-English language at home.
                Broken down by language:
                2.2% of residents speak Spanish at home,
                1.5% speak an Indo-European language, and
                0.5% speak an Asian language.

                </p>
                

                
    
        <h3 style="margin-top: 25px;" id="labor">
            Hopkinsville Income &amp; Labor Statistics
        </h3>
    


                
                
                    <h4>What is the unemployment rate in Hopkinsville, Kentucky?</h4>
                    <p>
                        The unemployment rate in Hopkinsville is 7.0%, which is calculated among residents aged 16 or older who are in the labor force.
                    </p>

                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Hopkinsville, Kentucky residents work for the government?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Hopkinsville, 18.6% of the
                    residents in the non-military labor force 
                    are employed by the local, state and federal government.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    

                
                
                    <h4>What is the median income in Hopkinsville, Kentucky?</h4>
                    <p>The median household income in Hopkinsville is $41,597.</p>
                

                
    
        <h3 style="margin-top: 25px;" id="housing">
            Hopkinsville Housing &amp; Rent Statistics
        </h3>
    


                
                
                <h4>What percentage of housing units are owner-occupied in Hopkinsville, Kentucky?</h4>
                <p>
                    In Hopkinsville, 49.7% of housing units
                    are occupied by their owners.
                </p>
                

                
                
                <h4>What percentage of housing units are rented in Hopkinsville, Kentucky?</h4>
                <p>
                    Renters occupy 50.3% of housing units in
                    Hopkinsville.
                </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Hopkinsville, Kentucky housing units were built before 1940?</h4>
                    <p>
                        Of all the housing units in Hopkinsville,
                        5.1% of them were build before 1940.
                    </p>
                

                
                

                
                    <h4>What percentage of Hopkinsville, Kentucky housing units were built after 2000?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Hopkinsville, 13.1% of the 
                    total housing units were built
                    
                        after the year 2000, which is approximately 
                        
                            1,900 units.
                        
                    
                    </p>
                
                
                
                
                <h4>What is the median monthly rent in Hopkinsville, Kentucky?</h4>
                <p>
                    The median gross monthly rent payment for renters in Hopkinsville is
                    $725.
                </p>

                

                
                
